Package org.anchoranalysis.image.voxel.convert

Converting Voxels to different data-types.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ToByte
    Base class for conversion to unsigned 8-bit.
    ToByteNoScaling
    Converts voxel buffers to a unsigned 8-bit buffer without scaling any values.
    ToByteScaleByMaxValue
    Converts voxel buffers to a unsigned 8-bit buffer linearly scaling against the maximum constant value.
    ToByteScaleByMinMaxValue
    Converts voxel buffers to a unsigned 8-bit buffer scaling against a the minimum and maximum constant.
    ToByteScaleByType
    Converts voxel buffers to a UnsignedByteBuffer scaling against the maximum value in each buffer.
    ToFloatNoScaling
    Converts voxel buffers to a FloatBuffer without scaling any values.
    ToShortNoScaling
    Converts voxel buffers to a unsigned 16-bit buffer without scaling any values.
    ToShortScaleByType
    Converts voxel buffers to a unsigned 16-bit buffer, scaling against the maximum value in each data-type.
    VoxelsConverter<T>
    Converts voxels from one data-type to another.
